  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "冒険はカードの中に！\n\n「キングダム ハーツ チェイン オブ メモリーズ」は、まったく新しい冒険を提供し、「キングダム ハーツ II」の舞台を整えます。ソラ、ドナルド、グーフィーは、行方不明の仲間を探して、広大で色とりどりの世界を旅します。お気に入りのディズニーやファイナルファンタジーの友達や敵と出会いましょう。\n\n新しい冒険への扉を開く神秘的なカードを集め、強力な能力を解放し、馴染みの友達を呼び寄せましょう。\n\n大迫力のグラフィックと高品質なアニメーションを体験してください。",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "romu"
    },
    {
      "text": "Kingdom Hearts: Chain of Memories is the second game in the Kingdom Hearts series. It is a direct sequel to Kingdom Hearts and exclusive to the Game Boy Advance. It was published by Square Enix and developed by Jupiter, and was released in 2004. Chronologically, it is the third game in the timeline after Kingdom Hearts Birth by Sleep and Kingdom Hearts, and takes place during Kingdom Hearts 358/2 Days.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "igdb"
    },
    {
      "text": "Kingdom Hearts: Chain of Memories takes place directly after the ending of the first game, Kingdom Hearts. The game is set in Castle Oblivion, a mysterious castle kept by Lord Marluxia. Sora and his teammates are told that the castle causes visitors to lose their memories upon entering. The lobby and areas between floors are white with flower-themed decorations, but each floor can be transformed into a different world from the first Kingdom Hearts game using \"world cards\" created from Sora's memories. Like before, many of the worlds are based on Disney films while the rest were created by Square Enix.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "igdb_storyline"
    },
